Dependencies: debhelper cmake doxygen libboost-dev libboost-test-dev libboost-system-dev libboost-thread-dev libboost-chrono-dev libboost-filesystem-dev libxml++2.6-dev libchimeratk-cppext-dev
Dependencies-dev: libboost-dev libboost-system-dev libboost-thread-dev libboost-chrono-dev libchimeratk-cppext-dev

Package-name-bin: mtca4u-deviceaccess-lmap-editor

Recommends-dev: libmtca4u-deviceaccess-doc
Enhances-doc: libmtca4u-deviceaccess-dev
Suggests-lib: #Package-name-bin#
Enhances-bin: #Package-name-lib#

Install-pattern-bin: usr/bin/mtca4u_lmap_editor.py

Description-dev: Header and cmake files for libmtca4u-deviceaccess. The files you need to compile against libmtca4u-deviceaccess.
Description-lib: mtca4u-deviceaccess provides a C++ API to access MTCA.4 devices. MTCA4U is a software package which provides divers, a C++ API and tools for hardware monitoring on MicroTCA.4 crates. mtca4u-deviceaccess is the C++ API which provides basic and generic access to the boards.
Description-doc: The doxygen html documentation for libmtca4u-deviceaccess and some examples.
Description-bin: GUI to create config files for the logical name mapping of DeviceAccess.
